org.sbml.jsbml

Class Annotation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.AnnotationElement
        • org.sbml.jsbml.Annotation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class Annotation
extends AnnotationElement
    An Annotation represents the annotations of an SBase element. It contains the list of CVTerm objects, a Map containing an XML name space and a String containing all the annotation elements of this name space.
    Since:
    0.8
    Version:
    $Rev: 2377 $
    Author:
    Marine Dumousseau, Andreas Dräger

        Parameters:

      • Annotation

        public Annotation(String annotation)
           throws XMLStreamException
        Creates an Annotation instance from a String containing non RDF annotation. By default, the History is null, the list of CVTerms is empty. The Map extensions is empty.
        Parameters:
        annotation - a String containing non RDF annotation, it will be parsed to create a Map containing an XML name space associated with a String representing all the annotation elements of this name space.
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException

      • Annotation

        public Annotation(String annotation,
          List<CVTerm> cvTerms)
           throws XMLStreamException
        Creates an Annotation instance from a String containing non RDF annotation and a list of CVTerm. By default, the History is null. The Map extensions is empty.
        Parameters:
        annotation - a String containing non RDF annotation, it will be parsed to create a Map containing an XML name space associated with a String representing all the annotation elements of this name space.
        cvTerms - the List of CVTerm.
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException

      • isSetAnnotation

        public boolean isSetAnnotation()
        Checks if the Annotation is initialized.

        An Annotation is initialized if at least one of the following is true:

        • there is some non RDF annotation
        • one or more CVTerm are defined
        • there is an history defined.
        Returns:
        true if the Annotation is initialized
